title: Malaysia Unemployment Rate
description: Unemployment Rate in Malaysia decreased to 3.60 percent in September from 3.70 percent in August of 2022. Unemployment Rate in Malaysia averaged 3.45 percent from 1998 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 5.30 percent in May of 2020 and a record low of 2.70 percent in August of 2012. In Malaysia, the unemployment rate measures the number of people actively looking for a job as a percentage of the labour force. This page provides - Malaysia Unemployment Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Department of Statistics, Malaysia
